name: AYANA Midplaza Jakarta
detail: The hotel is a good location, in the heart of Jakarta. Great facilities with Pool, sauna, spa, and fitness center which can make you relax and fresh. When afternoon time comes, I really enjoy afternoon cocktail at Rimba Ayana Jakarta. The room is clean and spacious space, but my room has an old tv. The hotel should change it with flat tv the new one. My bad experience coming from staff. From the first time, I arrive at the front door, no greeting, no smile, until i must wait 15-20 mins for check in, even when i have a breakfast, why there is no smile on your face and greetings? Please smile and your manner also need to improve. Greeting, smile , what ever the person is coming from. Over all, i'm realy enjoyed my staycation at Ayana Mid Plaza Jakarta. And Thank you for your smile and having time to share with humble one Mr. Christian Rene Hochtl, GM of Ayana Mid Plaza Hotel.

name: HARRIS Hotel & Conventions Kelapa Gading
detail: HARRIS Hotel and Conventions Kelapa Gading has always been my first choice when choosing a hotel in Jakarta. They have fun and friendly staffs that never stop smiling and the speed of checking in and out is extremely fast. The hotel offers clean, bright, large bedroom and of course fast-internet speed, both lan and wifi. The hotel is located next to a shopping mall, therefore looking for food and shopping is not an issue. After a long day out eating, and you are looking for a place to shred away those calories and sweat it off, do drop by the hotel gym. The hotel has a well-equip gym, sauna and swimming pool that opens until 2200hrs. During my stay with HARRIS Hotel, I was given a birthday gift, a birthday card and a birthday cake. I am impress with the CRM program of HARRIS Hotel and I would strongly recommend my friends to stay in HARRIS Hotel when they visit Jakarta.

name: The Grove Suites by GRAND ASTON
detail: The only hotel in Jakarta met my expectations. As I moved between 3 hotels all of them was 5 star but this hotel was a real modern 5 star. Great hotel connected to a shopping mall and it has great modern design everywhere, the room is super clean and comfortable. Without hesitation it will be my choice for my next business trip to Jakarta. I am highly recommending this hotel for all travelers.

name: Somerset Sudirman Jakarta
detail: Location is also pretty central but yet still a quiet place.

name: Ascott Jakarta
detail: It was the first time that The Husband and I travelled to Jakarta free and easy, without the help of guides. We were pleasantly surprised to discover the close proximity this hotel is to major shopping belts. To the left would be Thamrin City and to the right would be Grand Indonesia Shopping Town. Upon arrival at the airport, their airport transfer staff was there to bring us to the hotel. Upon registration, we were allowed to check-in immediately, even though it was only 11am and official check-in time wasn't until 2pm. Needless to say, we kept ourselves fully occupied with lots of shopping at the malls within that area. Dining choices were plenty. From Restoran Sederhana across from Thamrin City that sold delicious padang food, to foodcourts in Thamrin City for refresher meals in between shopping. Dinner would be a more relaxed affair over at Grand Indonesia Shopping Town. Again, spoilt for choice because they had more than 4 floors of food outlets accumulatively. From high end restaurants to foodcourts to suit your budget. Each time we returned to the hotel, we were greeted by warm smiles. On our last day, our scheduled pickup to the airport was at 230pm. We check with this staff if this meant we had to check-out at 12pm like with most hotels and leave our bags at the lobby while we spend the time away until 230pm, but they were nice enough to say that the room would be ours until the scheduled pick-up time. So Ascott Jakarta, we will be back. With friends and family in tow :)

name: HARRIS Suites fX Sudirman
detail: Harris FX is a great experience I can recommend to everybody in Jakarta, regardless if business, backpacker, couple or leisure traveller. Why? Because after having tried many other hotels in Jakarta, this was the first one that not only met my expectation but also exceeding it! Great rooms, great view (if on the 40s floors), great staff, great location (inside a shopping mall and next to other malls - if you know Jakarta you know how valuable this is), room equipment comprises all you need, refreshing room design, comfortable be and most of all - the price was in line withwhat you get - this is sthg I have never experienced before in Jakarta, regardless if luxury or 4-star hotel. Try it out yourself, I am sure you won't regret it.

name: YELLO Hotel Harmoni
detail: Pro: comfort bed, nice view from high floor, quiet, buffet breakfast many choices of food comparing to other 3 or 4 stars hotels in Jakarta, price worthy, toilet equipped with hair dryer, mini fridge provided Con: minor dirty brown stink on bed blanket, dirty stink not clean well on carpet below the chair, shower place no holder rack to put own things like shampoo, nearby no big mall but only a small mall next to hotel for food, not many street vendors nearby

name: Aston Kartika Grogol Hotel & Conference Center
detail: I reserved 2 rooms, 1 for my kids and another one is for me and my spouse. I've requested rooms with connecting door or close each other but the reality the front desk staff give 1 in the left corner and other one in the right corner although it is same floor, that makes me a bit disappointed, the front desk staff also didn't inform about the breakfast location and free parking when check in so i have to ask them actively. But, I feel satisfactory with the breakfast. It serves with many variants menu and taste good. The restaurant staff also helpful.

name: Vertu Harmoni Jakarta
detail: Harris Vertu hotel is something that outshines all the other hotels in the area. Located in Central Jakarta this hotel makes it easy to get to national landmarks like the Monas, Nayional Musuem and gallery and the Central Park area. Me and my partner arrived late to check out after so km e difficulties at the airport and Harris Hotel booked out the last standard room already and gave us a free upgrade without any issues at all. We collapsed as soon as we got to the room and the bed is incredibly comfortable and inviting. The room although small in size felt really big in actually because our room was situated in the corner of the hotel where we had two big windows to look out too thr city every morning and evening. We Not make much of the pool and other facilities such as pool and the spa was booked the last day we tried to use it. We went out during our 4 night stay so it was Not a big deal. I do have some smalls cons to point out. Bathroom: Sliding doorway and mirror is one and is behind the sink which Made it difficult to See full body in mirror. Dine in room service: of the few times we Did order room serverice they only got it half right. I think this is a miscommunication issue because we had to repeat our order several time. I think some of the staff have limited English capabilities. Also there are no vegetarian options on their menu you have to call to order/amend the menu which was frustrating at times because of miscommunication. Location: although it is close to many national landmarks it is not that close to many restaurants. Pros: Dine in Service: they were still open to accommodate to my vegetarian needs. Location: Close to grand indonesia mall and landmarks. I would glady stay at Harris Vertu again if I am in Jakarta and recommend others to do so.
